  "texts": [
    "In this context, the focus shifts from categorizing runs into 'healthy' and 'failure' classes to predicting the Remaining Useful Life (RUL) of the machinery.",
    "RUL represents the number of useful operational days remaining before a machine is expected to fail.",
    "Because RUL is a quantitative variable, the data imbalance issue doesn't apply.",
    "The regression path employs the same approach as the classification path to handle temporal dependence.",
    "LSTM architecture is utilized to learn temporal features from the GAN-generated data, which are valuable in training ML algorithms to predict the Remaining Useful Life (RUL)."
  ],
